    "causal_summary": "When the code graph is empty (never built, or reset), the read tools (`code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`) return `status:\"blocked\"` with `requiredAction: code_graph_scan` — they never build the index themselves. For a fresh repo clone (whose scope is just its own `/src` code), that forces a manual scan before the graph is useful, even though building from empty is safe (nothing to overwrite).",
